    Black Aracnia took out a needle filled with a seditive that would ease 
Darkmouse into a peaceful sleep. It would let her body repair its self. 
Coming back from the dead was a hard thing to go through, but the mouse was 
taking it well.
    She inserted the needle into her right arm and let the medicine flow 
through her viens with the energon. Thw widow could now leave her, knowing 
she would be safe from harm. The worst part was over, tommorow she would be 
up and running like nothing happened. 
    Leaveing the room, she recalled Quickstrike being rather depressed. He 
could keep a vigil over Darkmouse while she was attending Megatron. Walking 
down the corridor she entered the alcove to his quarters. They were one of 
the largest on the ship. Originally ment for the senior staff, but in times 
of war.....
    She pused the keypad, and entered. In the great room of his quarters lay 
chairs, sofas, tables, and art work recreated digitally by some of the 
greatest Predacon, and even Decepticon artist ever. She made her way through 
the room to enter the hall way that led to his chamber. With her black claw 
she scrapped softly.
    "Quickstrike? I want to talk to you about Darkmouse. Quickstrike?" She 
asked agian softly, comfortly.
